  * ![](http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2011/11/02/Darkblade/d85dc481-c84a-41ba-b9d8-db0b657ebc3d/60x60.png) Darkblade

12 January 2012 12:26PM

Perhaps it's that people who have certain things going on in their brain
(chemically) are more prone to certain kinds of behaviour, particularly those
that block out less pleasant aspects of life. An 'addictive personality', if
you like (much as it has become some kind of buzz-phrase). This could include
drug or alcohol use but also things like online gambling or just using the
internet excessively in general, at the milder (less physically harmful) end
of the spectrum.

