Incidentally (and I should have stated this in my first post)....PERMANENT
change to brain chemistry is a different matter. My criticism is that simply
saying 'x causes a change to brain activity' doesn't tell us whether it's a
permanent change (and even then, the relationship can be complex), or the kind
of normal change we constantly undergo.

