Why is Italy in trouble?

8 Nov 2011

Italians have low personal debt, the second biggest manufacturing economy in
Europe and Berlusconi claims the restaurants in Rome are full. So why is Italy
now at the centre of the eurozone crisis? Polly Curtis, with your help, finds
out. Get in touch below the line, email your views to
